Private API Document
Introduction
This document outlines only the Private API endpoints. These API require you to have an API key
and Secret from the “Developers” section of your NestEx account.
We try to and will continue to maintain these endpoints in terms of uptime, availability and data
accuracy. In the event of any problems with these API endpoints please connect with us on
support@nestex.one
At this time, all endpoints are considered EXPERIMENTAL. Please use it with SMALL AMOUNTS
and AT YOUR OWN RISK.
Base URL for these API is https://trade.nestex.one/api/v2/[API ENDPOINT]
For more information, please refer to the following section:
Section A: Informational API
A.0: Check Token (basic validity test)
A.1: Balances
A.2: Orders (Unfulfilled)
A.3: Trades
Section B: Transactional API
B.1: Place Limit Order
B.2: Cancel Order
All data is in JSON format. You are required to adhere to a MINIMUM TIME GAP of 5 seconds
between API hits for ALL THE API noted here.
Again I reiterate, although all endpoints are tested, they are considered EXPERIMENTAL until
further notice. Trades made cannot be reversed, so errors of any kind can have a price. Please
use it with SMALL AMOUNTS and AT YOUR OWN RISK.
For ALL APIs noted in this document, you must provide a minimum input of the form:
Note: IN THE POST REQUEST, NOT THE HEADERS.{
"apikey": "{api key taken from the developers section}",
"apisecret": "{api secret taken from the developers section}"
}A. Informational API
Endpoints Overview
No.Endpoint
Description
A.0./checktokenChecks if the api key + secret used is valid or not.
A.1./balancesList of balances and locked amounts of all coins where the
balance is non-zero
A.2./ordersGives you a list of your unfulfilled orders (i.e. ‘open’ and ‘partial’
orders only)
Miscellaneous response parameters:
1. TTL = Time taken to execute the request in milliseconds. If this is very long (more than
400) it may help to check your network; if the issue persists get in touch with us via the
support tickets.
2. “success”: “ok” = This is an indicative response that the request was received and
processed. This does not guarantee perfect or instant fulfillment of any orders placed; it
simply assures that orders have been placed in the book. Likewise for cancellations.
